# Story 1.8a: Weave Path Generation UI

Status: ready-for-dev

<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->

## Story

As a **new user completing onboarding**,
I want to **see a visually engaging loading state and then review my AI-generated goal breakdown**,
So that **I understand my path forward and feel excited to begin my transformation**.

## Acceptance Criteria

### AC #1: Loading Animation ("Shaping your path...")
- [ ] Display loading screen immediately after user confirms their first Needle in Story 1.7
- [ ] Show animated Weave logo or thread-weaving animation (subtle, magical)
- [ ] Display text: "Shaping your path..." (centered, semi-bold)
- [ ] Loading screen displays while AI processes (actual duration varies 1-10s based on AI response time)
- [ ] Minimum display time: 1 second (prevents flash for fast responses <1s)
- [ ] Smooth fade-in animation when loading screen appears
- [ ] NO spinner - use thread/weave animation for brand consistency (reuse from Story 1.6)
- [ ] **CRITICAL**: This is a loading placeholder while waiting for AI response from Story 1.8b API
- [ ] Show message "Taking longer than usual..." after 10 seconds
- [ ] Show timeout error with retry option after 15 seconds total

### AC #2: AI Breakdown Display Structure
- [ ] Once AI response received, fade out loading screen
- [ ] Display AI-generated breakdown in card-based layout:
  - **Goal Title & Summary** (top card)
  - **2-3 Milestones** (middle section, stacked cards)
  - **2-4 Binds** (bottom section, stacked cards)
- [ ] Each section has a visual separator (thread line or subtle divider)
- [ ] Cards use liquid-glass aesthetic (consistent with onboarding design)
- [ ] Typography: Title (semi-bold, large), body text (medium, 90% opacity)
- [ ] Adequate spacing between cards (spacing[4] = 16px minimum)

### AC #3: Goal Title & Summary Card
- [ ] Display AI-generated goal title (1-2 lines, large text)
- [ ] Display goal summary paragraph (2-4 sentences, medium text)
- [ ] Card at top of screen, full-width with padding
- [ ] Subtle animation on appearance (fade + slight upward drift)
- [ ] Read-only display (edit capability comes later in AC #5)

### AC #4: Milestones Section
- [ ] Display 2-3 AI-generated milestones as individual cards
- [ ] Each milestone shows:
  - Milestone number (1, 2, 3)
  - Milestone title (1 line, bold)
  - Optional: Brief description (1 sentence, lighter text)
- [ ] Milestones appear with staggered animation (each card 100ms delay)
- [ ] Visual hierarchy: Numbered, sequential presentation
- [ ] Cards stack vertically with consistent spacing

### AC #5: Binds (Actions/Habits) Section
- [ ] Display 2-4 AI-generated binds as individual cards
- [ ] Each bind shows:
  - Bind name (1 line, bold)
  - Bind description (1-2 sentences describing the action)
  - Optional: Frequency indicator (e.g., "Daily" or "3x/week")
- [ ] Binds appear with staggered animation after milestones
- [ ] Visual design emphasizes actionability (checkmark icon, action-oriented language)
- [ ] Cards stack vertically with consistent spacing

### AC #6: Edit Functionality
- [ ] Each section (goal, milestones, binds) has an "Edit" button or pencil icon
- [ ] Tapping "Edit" opens inline edit mode for that section
- [ ] Inline edit:
  - Input field replaces display text
  - User can modify content
  - "Save" and "Cancel" buttons appear
  - Save updates local state
  - Cancel reverts to AI-generated content
- [ ] Edited content is visually marked (e.g., subtle yellow highlight or "edited" badge)
- [ ] All edits persist until user either:
  - Accepts the full breakdown (AC #7)
  - Navigates back to regenerate (AC #8)

### AC #7: Accept CTA
- [ ] Fixed bottom button: "Looks good" or "Start my journey"
- [ ] Button full-width, primary color, touch-optimized (min 48px height)
- [ ] Button enabled by default (user can accept immediately or edit first)
- [ ] On tap:
  - Store final breakdown (AI-generated + edits) in state
  - Navigate to Story 1.9 (First Commitment Ritual)
  - Smooth transition animation

### AC #8: Optional "Regenerate" / "Edit Goal" CTA
- [ ] Optional secondary button or link: "Edit my goal" or back navigation
- [ ] If user taps back:
  - Return to Story 1.7 (goal input screen)
  - Preserve their edited breakdown in case they return
  - Allow user to resubmit goal for new AI generation
- [ ] Confirmation dialog if user has made edits: "You'll lose your edits. Continue?"

### AC #9: Error Handling
- [ ] If AI call fails (Story 1.8b returns error):
  - Show friendly error message: "Couldn't generate your path. Let's try again."
  - CTA: "Retry" button to resubmit goal to AI
  - Alternative: "Choose a template" to use deterministic fallback
- [ ] If AI call times out (>10 seconds):
  - Show message: "Taking longer than usual... Still working on it."
  - After 15 seconds total: Show timeout error with retry option
- [ ] Network connectivity check: Show offline banner if no internet

### AC #10: Data Flow & State Management
- [ ] Receive AI response from Story 1.8b via props, context, or async state
- [ ] Store breakdown in component state:
  ```typescript
  {
    goal_title: string,
    goal_summary: string,
    milestones: Array<{id: string, title: string, description?: string}>,
    binds: Array<{id: string, name: string, description: string, frequency?: string}>,
    edited_sections: Array<'goal' | 'milestone_0' | 'bind_1' | ...>
  }
  ```
- [ ] On "Looks good", pass final breakdown to next screen (Story 1.9)
- [ ] **DEFERRED**: Database writes happen in Story 1.9 or later backend integration

### AC #11: Accessibility & UX Polish
- [ ] Loading animation respects reduced motion preferences
- [ ] Card animations respect reduced motion (fade-only, no complex motion)
- [ ] Touch targets meet minimum 48px x 48px requirement
- [ ] Edit buttons clearly labeled for screen readers
- [ ] Contrast ratios meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- [ ] Keyboard navigation support (if applicable for web later)

### AC #12: Performance Requirements
- [ ] Screen renders immediately after AI response (<100ms)
- [ ] Animations run at 60fps (smooth, no jank)
- [ ] Edit mode transitions are instant (<50ms)
- [ ] Total interaction time <30 seconds (AC #7 completion)

